From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: buildroot <buildroot@buildroot.org>
Date: Thu, 13 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] meson.build: fix build when systemd is not found

When systemd is not found and systemd-unit-prefix is not set,
the variable systemd_system_unit_dir is never defined, causing
meson to error out with "Unknown variable". Initialize it to
an empty string so the conditional on line 37 works correctly.

Signed-off-by: buildroot <buildroot@buildroot.org>
---
 meson.build | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/meson.build b/meson.build
index 1111111..2222222 100644
--- a/meson.build
+++ b/meson.build
@@ -16,6 +16,7 @@ add_project_arguments('-DHAVE_ZSTD', language : 'c')
 # Not required to build the executable,
 # only to automatically retrieve the install dir for unit files
 systemd = dependency('systemd', required : false)
+systemd_system_unit_dir = ''
 if get_option('systemd-unit-prefix') != ''
   systemd_system_unit_dir = get_option('systemd-unit-prefix')
 elif systemd.found()
